[Canyon County, with a population was 188 923 in 2010, is located in the southwestern part of the U.S. state of Idaho (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canyon_County,_Idaho). It is the 2nd-most populous county in Idaho and is part of the Boise Metropolitan Statistical Area. The city of Boise, east of Canyon County, is the capital and most populous city in Idaho.

For discussions of the rising incidence of syphilis in men who have sex with men, see my moderator comments in prior ProMED-mail posts below. - Mod.ML

